# Data layer — Supabase

## Migrations
- One change = one timestamped migration in `supabase/migrations`. Never edit an applied migration.
- Every table: RLS enabled + policies + indexes in the same file. Geography columns get GIST indexes.
- Visibility checks reuse helpers `public.can_view(owner_id, visibility)` / `public.is_mutual_follow` from `0001_init.sql`.
- After schema changes run `pnpm gen:types` (wraps `supabase gen types typescript --local > packages/types/src/database.ts`).

## packages/api structure
- `src/supabase/client.ts` (browser, `@supabase/ssr`), `src/supabase/server.ts` (cookies), `src/supabase/env.ts`.
- One module per domain: `pins.ts`, `chapters.ts`, `trails.ts`, `media.ts`, `social.ts`, `profile.ts`.
- Every function: explicit input/output types from `@imprint/types`; mappers convert DB rows (snake_case, WKB/GeoJSON geography) → domain types (camelCase, `{lng,lat}`). Mappers live in `src/mappers.ts` and have unit tests (Vitest).
- Errors: throw typed `ApiError` with a code; never swallow Supabase errors silently.

## Query rules
- Reading someone else's pins: ONLY the `pins_visible` view. Own pins for editing may use `memory_pins`.
- Bounds queries: pass bbox, filter with PostGIS on the server (RPC if PostgREST operators are not enough), never fetch-all-then-filter on the client.
- Lists are paginated (keyset by `pinned_at, id`), default page 50.
- TanStack Query keys are arrays with stable serialization: `['pins', {bbox, chapterId, from, to}]`. Mutations invalidate the narrowest keys possible and use optimistic updates for create-pin and reactions.

## Storage
- Bucket `media` (private). Path: `{user_id}/{pin_id}/{uuid}.webp`. Policies: users write only under their own `{user_id}/` prefix. Reads via signed URLs from `media.getSignedUrls(pinId)` which relies on RLS of `pin_media`.
